cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the use of convolutional neural networks for the semantic classification of remote sensing scenes. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained networks and fine-tuning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve the use of large datasets, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for performance improvement, which is a common theme in neural networks (cs.NE).
